<collectingCountry id="F33B766DFFE55551195940AC4082FC16" box="[361,470,986,1012]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(endemic).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9336FDFFE55551188D408940A0FB12" blockId="1.[136,1452,914,1265]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
Note:—In 
<collectingCountry id="F33B766DFFE555511905408840F1FBFA" box="[309,421,1022,1048]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D7EFFE55551199F40894307FBFA" authorityName="Ranil" authorityYear="2010" box="[431,595,1022,1049]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Cyatheaceae" genus="Cyathea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyatheales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="srilankensis">
<emphasis id="B958EAEFFFE55551199F40894307FBFA" box="[431,595,1022,1049]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">A. srilankensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remotely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D7EFFE555511B08408945FBFBFB" authority="(Thwaites) R. M. Tryon" authorityName="R. M. Tryon" baseAuthorityName="Thwaites" box="[824,1199,1022,1049]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Cyatheaceae" genus="Alsophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyatheales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hookeri">
<emphasis id="B958EAEFFFE555511B08408942F9FBFA" box="[824,941,1022,1049]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">A. hookeri</emphasis>
(Thwaites) R.M.Tryon
</taxonomicName>
from which it is easily distinguished by its larger trunk and leaves as well as by its pinnate to pinnatisect pinnae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B0CFFE555511CB547544409FBDF" author="Ranil, R. H. G. &amp; Pushpakumara, D. K. N. G. &amp; Janssen, T. &amp; Wijesundara, D. S. A. &amp; Dhanasekara, D. U. M. B." box="[1157,1373,1058,1085]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" pagination="39 - 44" refId="ref2390" refString="Ranil, R. H. G., Pushpakumara, D. K. N. G., Janssen, T., Wijesundara, D. S. A. &amp; Dhanasekara, D. U. M. B. (2010 b) Cyathea srilankensis Ranil (Cyatheaceae): A new tree fern species from Sri Lanka. American Fern Journal 100: 39 - 44. https: // doi. org / 10.1640 / 0002 - 8444 - 100.1.39" type="journal article" year="2010">
Ranil 
<emphasis id="B958EAEFFFE555511CFB47554450FBDE" box="[1227,1284,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">et al.</emphasis>
, 2010b
</bibRefCitation>
). Also, it was clear that 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D7EFFE555511975473140B8FB82" authorityName="Ranil" authorityYear="2010" box="[325,492,1094,1121]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Cyatheaceae" genus="Cyathea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyatheales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="srilankensis">
<emphasis id="B958EAEFFFE555511975473140B8FB82" box="[325,492,1094,1121]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">A. srilankensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat morphologically similar only to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D7EFFE555511BC94730445CFB82" authority="J. Sm." authorityName="J. Sm." box="[1017,1288,1094,1120]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Cyatheaceae" genus="Alsophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyatheales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis id="B958EAEFFFE555511BC9473045EBFB82" box="[1017,1215,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Alsophila humilis</emphasis>
J.Sm.
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="F33B766DFFE555511898471C4059FB66" box="[168,269,1130,1156]" name="Tanzania" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F33B766DFFE55551197B471D40C3FB67" box="[331,407,1131,1157]" name="Kenya" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Kenya</collectingCountry>
, and to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D7EFFE5555119C9471C4204FB66" authority="Reimers" authorityName="Reimers" box="[505,848,1130,1156]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Cyatheaceae" genus="Alsophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyatheales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schliebenii">
<emphasis id="B958EAEFFFE5555119C9471C43BCFB66" box="[505,744,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Alsophila schliebenii</emphasis>
Reimers
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F33B766DFFE555511B4B471C42B7FB66" box="[891,995,1130,1156]" name="Tanzania" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
. Though, Holttum (1981) suggested an affinity of Sri Lankan tree ferns with African elements, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B0CFFE555511ACD47F942B2FB4A" author="Janssen, T. &amp; Rakotonduainibe, F." box="[765,998,1166,1193]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" pagination="221 - 376" refId="ref2239" refString="Janssen, T. &amp; Rakotonduainibe, F. (2008) A revision of the indusiate scaly tree ferns (Cyatheaceae, Cyathea subgen. Alsophila sect. Alsophila) in Madagascar, the Comoros and the seychlles. Adansonia 30: 221 - 376." type="journal article" year="2008">
Janssen 
<emphasis id="B958EAEFFFE555511B6B47F942C0FB4A" box="[859,916,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
claimed that Sri Lankan tree ferns form a monophyletic group not closely related to African tree ferns. However, the phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D7EFFE555511D3647C544F8FB2E" authorityName="Ranil" authorityYear="2010" box="[1286,1452,1202,1229]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Cyatheaceae" genus="Cyathea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyatheales" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="srilankensis">
<emphasis id="B958EAEFFFE555511D3647C544F8FB2E" box="[1286,1452,1202,1229]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">A. srilankensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains to be further elucidated.
</paragraph>
